author: Carl Lamarre
title: Wale Releases 'Fashion Week' Feat. G-Eazy | Billboard
text:
Dante Marshall Wale 
Since the top of the year, Wale has been on a hot streak with new music. He continues his run by hitting the runaway with G-Eazy for his new release "Fashion Week." 
"Ah, find me a Kendall Jenner, I'll be a gentleman to her," Wale raps in the intro. With repetitive chants of "go, switch" on the chorus, the MMG MC and Bay Area spitter prove to be a formidable duo in search of America's next top model. 
Earlier this month, Wale dropped the visual for his Lil Wayne-assisted track " Running Back ," and recently sprinkled some bars over a remix of Ed Sheeran's No. 1 single "Shape of You." He is also prepping his fifth studio effort, Shine.
